\"last commit\"> Localizing contents text in Blazor (<a href=\"https://jsakamoto.github.io/Toolbelt.Blazor.I18nText/\">Demo</a>).</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-25T10:50:51.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries &#x26; Extensions</h2><h3>Tools &#x26; Utilities</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/klemmchr/MvvmBlazor\">MvvmBlazor</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/klemmchr/MvvmBlazor\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">181</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":181,\"repo\":\"klemmchr/MvvmBlazor\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/github/stars/klemmchr/MvvmBlazor?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=604800\" alt=\"stars\"> <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/github/last-commit/klemmchr/MvvmBlazor?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=86400\" alt=\"last commit\"> BlazorMVVM is a small framework for building Blazor and BlazorServerside apps. With it's simple to use MVVM pattern you can boost up your development speed while minimizing the hazzle to just make it work.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-25T10:50:51.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Career</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://jacobian.org/2019/apr/23/questions-for-employers-director-vp/\">My questions for prospective employers (Director/VP roles)</a> - Be prepared to ask them as a recruiter or being asked about them for senior management roles.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-25T10:13:23.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Career</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>“Since managers are not tied to a sector (in the way nurses or musicians are), the good ones tend to go where they are payed good money and the bad ones end up wreaking havoc where they are payed at least some money. That, also, is <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baumol%27s_cost_disease\">Baumol</a> in action.” (<a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=20448929\">source</a>) - Explains how the pool of professional managers gets distributed into the various sectors of the economy.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-25T10:13:23.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Career</h2><h3>Promotion</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://workplace.stackexchange.com/questions/145709/how-to-discipline-overeager-engineer\">How to discipline overeager engineer</a> - Over-achieving talent is looking for a management promotion. Management does not recognize effort. Engineer become disgruntled and management is looking to discipline him. A case-study of a bad situation in which both side shows clumsiness.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-25T10:13:23.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Career</h2><h3>Performance Reviews</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.joelonsoftware.com/2000/04/03/incentive-pay-considered-harmful/\">Incentive Pay Considered Harmful</a> - “Incentives (or bribes) simply can't work in the workplace. (…) Most software managers have no choice but to go along with performance review systems that are already in place. If you're in this position, the only way to prevent teamicide is to simply give everyone on your team a gushing review”.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-25T10:13:23.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Career</h2><h3>Performance Reviews</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>“If anything in your performance review is a surprise, then I have failed as a manager.” (<a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=17249767\">source</a>).</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-25T10:13:23.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Career</h2><h3>Performance Reviews</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>“This is what I loved about working at Netflix. We didn't have performance reviews. It was assumed that your performance was good to excellent, otherwise you wouldn't be working there anymore. You had a constant feedback loop with your manager on performance, but nothing was ever formal.” (<a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=23861960\">source</a>).</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-25T10:13:23.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Career</h2><h3>Performance Reviews</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>“The system a software developer works in shapes their performance so much more than individual differences.” (<a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=21972033\">source</a>).</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-25T10:13:23.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"antdimot/awesome-lowcode","categoryHTML":"<h2>Automation</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.appian.com/\">Appian</a> - Discover the power of low-code automation.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-08-25T09:51:34.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"tortuvshin/open-source-flutter-apps","categoryHTML":"<h3>Finance</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/yash1200/bank_management\">Bank Git</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/yash1200/bank_management\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=